<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/67601AVHPCSTMMBKTGKLCGLQQCGMMBVSK> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Heroes Reimagined";
  schema:description """
	PRE-CONCERT TALK 6:30PM   CONCERT 7:30PM  <span><br/></span>GUEST CONDUCTOR: Nadege Foofat <span><br/></span>GUEST ARTIST: Marika Bournaki, Piano<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Three different centuries, three different visions of heroism - modern, intimate, and ultimately, triumphant. The programme reimagines courage today, while taking us on a journey of inner reflection, self-expression and ultimate bravery.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Programme:<span><br/></span>Kelly Marie MURPHY: On Rethinking Heroism in the 21st Century<span><br/></span>SCHUMANN: Piano Concerto in A minor, Op. 54<span><br/></span>BEETHOVEN: Symphony No. 3, in E flat Major, Op. 55 “Eroica” <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Read more about the Vancouver Island Symphony, Guest Artists and the music at <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.vancouverislandsymphony.com\"> www.vancouverislandsymphony.com</a> <span class=\"ItalicText\">Driven by Passion. United in Sound</span><span><br/></span>Stay updated on <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/vanislesymphony\"> Facebook</a> and <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/vancouverislandsymphony/\"> Instagram</a>
""";
