<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/62001APSGSQLCTLTNJRSTDSVSMQBNHTVL> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "In Spite of Ourselves - Tickets Available at Door";
  schema:description """
	Initially not much more than a good natured musical one-off between friends, the West Coast quartet <span class=\"BoldText\">In Spite of Ourselves</span> has evolved into a highly entertaining act with a mission — to keep alive the deep and timeless catalogue of songwriter John Prine.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>An unspoken understanding of this mission is the belief that there are only two kinds of people in the musical world: those whose lives have been profoundly changed by Prine, and those who haven’t heard him yet.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">In Spite of Ourselves: A Celebration of the Music of John Prine</span> brings together the interpretive talents of multi-instrumentalist/producer Doug Cox, Juno Award-winning Tom and Kalissa Landa from the Paperboys, and Nashville/Vancouver Island songwriter/artist Steve Mitchell. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All lifelong Prine devotees, the members of In Spite of Ourselves take turns diving deep into the Prine songbook. With a twinkle in his eye, Doug Cox leads the band through a joyously loose reading of Prine’s “You Got Gold” featuring a drunken-sounding orchestra of fiddle, harmonica, and melodica. Tom Landa finds the tender and contemplative heart of “Long Monday,” and Steve Mitchell goes over to the other side of the tracks on the funky “Mexican Home.” And on “Picture Show,” Kalissa Landa follows up the song’s insanely hooky chorus with a fiddle solo that’s as combustible as an old film projector. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tragically for all of us, John Prine left this world at the beginning of the pandemic. But thanks to his songs, music fans everywhere have a permanent portal into the little universe of his singular mind. In Spite of Ourselves takes you through that door and shows you the house that John Prine built. You’re never going to want to leave. 
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-04-14T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/files/fa91eff0-11f0-4e04-8862-34431c5216c7.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/location/412AHMGMKLQDMMDQBVNMGMNLDCBBPTLQP>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/organization/got-pop?-concerts>;
  schema:keywords "Offsite Events";
  schema:duration "PT120M";
  schema:endDate "2026-04-14T21:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/34201ASMCSDCJKPKGCLJTKVRDGQJPPMJH> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Infinity RUSH - The RUSH Experience";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Infinity RUSH</span></span> deliver an authentic concert experience that captures the spirit of one of the world’s most successful musical groups of all-time.  A <span class=\"ItalicText\">RUSH</span> tribute show that embodies an energy that is greater than the sum of its parts, that is as close as it gets to the real thing.  <span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>This compelling tribute show accurately emulates <span class=\"ItalicText\">RUSH</span> both vocally and instrumentally, in a show laden with impressive renditions of the very best hit songs and fan favorites. An audio and visual extravaganza that fully and completely satisfies!<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Members of <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Infinity RUSH</span></span> have performed on marquee stages with members of: Asia, Journey, Foreigner, Kansas, Santana, Chicago, Boston, The Tubes, Van Halen, Styx, Toto, Starship, The Who, Judas Priest, Jeff Beck and other acclaimed recording artists, and have shared the stage with Charlie Pride, Steve Vai, Tommy Shaw, Neal Schon, Steve Lukather, Sammy Hagar, Lou Gramm, Bill Champlain and Fee Waybill.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">\"When I close my eyes, it's hard to tell the difference\"</span> - Tony Geranios (Geddy Lee – Keyboard Tech) <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Enjoy this memorable and captivating note-for-note event, that captures the magic of <span class=\"ItalicText\">RUSH</span>. 
""";
