<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/65201ACRNVHVJBDMGRPJPBKVMQHKPTNJN> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Island Bel Canto: Our Backyard - Tickets Available at Door";
  schema:description """
	Two of Vancouver Island’s distinguished adult treble choirs join forces to present an evening of Canadian favourites – all composed by women.<span><br/></span>Island Bel Canto will perform songs of Joni Mitchell (Circle Game), Susan Crowe (Sparrow) and Jane Siberry (The Valley). Other compositions include: a song about a Malaysian fish (Ikan Kekek); a description of the sleek Canadian mammal (Otter); also, amazing Canadian arrangements of Aurora’s Apple Tree, Eastern Owl’s Warrior, and an uplifting composition titled Light, by Montreal’s Marie-Claire Saindon (to a poem by Rabindranath Tagore).<span><br/></span>Guest artists Encore! Women’s Choir, based in Duncan, will present their own set of Canadian favourites, including Joni Mitchell’s Both Sides Now.<span><br/></span>Both choirs – with over 50 soaring voices – will sing Connie Kaldor’s Wood River, a hilarious rendition of A Place in the Choir, and a new song by Vancouver Island composer, Deborah Sumner - Our Backyard.<span><br/></span>What better way to spend a spring evening, than to enjoy music that is uplifting, amusing and just plain fun? … all in “our own backyard”!<span><br/></span>
""";
