<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/63401AKSVRPNGHKKCCHMBDJQTCPLNPCTK> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Luke Wallace - Tickets available at the Door";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Tickets available at the Door</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Experience the vibrant energy of Vancouver singer-songwriter Luke Wallace, live in concert! A modern-day Pete Seeger, Luke is more than a gifted singer-songwriter—he is a community builder and a musical ambassador for peace and the planet, sharing his folk-inspired songs with audiences across North America, India, the UK, and beyond. Known for his engaging stage presence, he invites the audience to join in and sing, creating a warm, interactive experience where everyone feels part of the music.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Luke Wallace is a dynamic force in the world of folk music, using his talent as a songwriter, speaker, and choral arranger to stand up for peace and environmental protection, and to inspire positive change. Hailing from the Coast Salish Territory known as Vancouver, Canada, Luke has been on a decade-long journey of touring, recording, and organizing for the betterment of people and the planet.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>In 2023, Luke took the global stage as a feature performer at the United Nations Water Conference, the first of its kind in a generation. With hundreds of concerts across North America under his belt, and his unique brand of socially-conscious folk, Luke has earned a loyal following and a reputation as a modern-day Pete Seeger, spreading a message of hope and action through his music.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Armed with folk, a little rap, call and response, a poet's gift and a voice to deliver it all, Luke is both an artist to listen to and a hope for the future.”</span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">- Gary Cristall, The Vancouver Folk Music Festival</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Luke Wallace very much loves and appreciates where he comes from: BC and the Coast Salish Territory, and he defends that territory in song with passionate style. Once you hear Luke Wallace, you can imagine how well his music goes over at the folk festivals he plays. As a coastal kid myself, Luke's music certainly stirs my emotions as well. He's a true West Coast gem.”</span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">- Grant Lawrence, CBC host, author, goalie</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Learn more about Luke and his music at <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.lukewallacemusic.com\">www.lukewallacemusic.com</a><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Show Opener:<span><br/></span>Sylvia Humble is a folk-inspired singer-songwriter known for her pure heartfelt vocals, rhythmic ukulele strumming, and engaging performance style. Influenced by artists such as Joni Mitchell and Coco Love Alcorn — with whom she has performed — she brings warmth, passion, and deep musical joy to the stage. Singing songs that raise hopes and spirits written by some of her favourite artists as well as her own originals, Sylvia will be joined in this opening set by April Laurie and Jude Wong to craft a harmony-rich experience, inviting the audience to lend their voices along the way. A devoted songleader and member of the Ubuntu Choirs Network, she is passionate about building community and making the world a better place through singing together in (imperfect) harmony. Learn more about Sylvia and her community singing events <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.sylviahumble.ca/events\">on her website</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
