<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/69801ACHMQQPHNNNRPKGGCKPVPDJPPBTJ> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Ride to Resilience Film Premier";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Age restriction: 13 years and up</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Ride to Resilience is a powerful feature-length documentary that dives into the unseen mental battles faced by first responders, athletes, and everyday people who are expected to carry it all.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Following firefighter and professional mountain biker <span class=\"BoldText\">Steve Vanderhoek</span>, the film traces a two-year journey shaped by trauma, loss, and healing, both on the trail and off. The story explores how depression and PTSD can quietly build beneath a capable exterior, and how connection, vulnerability, peer support and community can become lifelines.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Mature Subject Matter Notice</span><span><br/></span>This film contains mature themes, including discussions of mental health, depression, PTSD, suicide, traumatic emergency incidents, and loss. While there is no graphic content, some subject matter may be emotionally challenging. Viewer discretion is advised.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.ridetoresilience.ca/\"> www.ridetoresilience.ca</a>
""";
