<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/64401AKMPPVDBDCMHSBTMJNCMMKKJJJDG> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Singing Workshop: Luke Wallace/Sylvia Humble - Tickets available at the Door";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Tickets available at the Door</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Singing Workshop</span> takes place inside the Hall at the St. Andrew's United Church on <span class=\"BoldText\">Saturday, April 18 @ 12:30PM</span> (One day after the April 17 Luke Wallace concert). This is a standalone event and requires one admission per entry.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This inclusive <span class=\"BoldText\">Singing Workshop</span> invites singers of all ages and experienced levels to dive deeper into Luke Wallace’s uplifting original songs, in a collaborative community singing experience centered on connection and caring for the world we share. Through call-and-response teaching, Luke creates a relaxed and joyful space where everyone can participate—no sheet music or prior singing experience required. Luke’s songs are currently being sung by 85 community choirs around the world, giving participants a chance to engage with music that has inspired singers globally. No prior singing experience or sheet music is needed—just bring your voice and enthusiasm! The workshop is presented by community song leader Sylvia Humble.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Please note the Singing Workshop is a TICKET-LESS event. All ticket purchasers will be on a list at the door for entry into the Hall for the workshop</span>
""";
