<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/76401ADQTCVSBMHNJBVTLKRDDQKCTSTRJ> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "SPOTLIGHT: CaneFire";
  schema:description """
	CARIBBEAN LATIN JAZZ<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“<span class=\"ItalicText\">If Dizzy Gillespie were still with us, he would love CaneFire.</span>” - <span class=\"BoldText\">Vancouver Sun</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Toronto-based Caribbean jazz powerhouse <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">CaneFire</span></span> is NOT your grandfather’s jazz band. As one of the most explosive and energetic jazz ensembles on the planet, <span class=\"ItalicText\">CaneFire</span> delivers a rollicking, high-octane show combining the white-hot energy of Cuban rhythm, the blinding musicianship of modern jazz, and the unbridled joy of the music of the Caribbean.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">CaneFire’s</span> signature sound revolves around its unconventional use of the steelpan – the only petroleum byproduct in the world that is actually good for you. Led by Canadian pianist/composer <span class=\"BoldText\">Jeremy Ledbetter</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">CaneFire</span> also features steelpan virtuoso <span class=\"BoldText\">Mark Mosca</span>, <span class=\"BoldText\">Alexis Baro</span> (trumpet), <span class=\"BoldText\">Braxton Hicks</span> (saxophones), <span class=\"BoldText\">Chendy Leon</span> (drums), <span class=\"BoldText\">Yoser Rodriguez</span> (bass), and <span class=\"BoldText\">Alberto Suarez</span> (percussion).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">CaneFire</span> has released two albums and taken their unique brand of Caribbean Latin Jazz from BC to Newfoundland, to South America, and to the Caribbean, including three years in a row at the Trinidad and Tobago Jazz Festival. Their second album <span class=\"ItalicText\">Pandemonium</span> embodies all the sizzle and twice the sophistication of its predecessor, and features guest performances by Trinidadian calypso superstar <span class=\"BoldText\">David Rudder</span> and Brazilian jazz legend <span class=\"BoldText\">Hermeto Pascoal</span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“<span class=\"ItalicText\">CaneFire is sweeter than Caroni brown sugar, and don’t doubt me.</span>” - <span class=\"BoldText\">Trinidad Guardian</span>
""";
