<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/75201AGVRCJPJLNTHDCBKRGQMKMBJJLBP> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "SPOTLIGHT: GLOB";
  schema:description """
	MONTREAL FAMILY CIRCUS<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Full of surprises, circus charm, and magical moments!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Glob</span></span> is a fun, family event full of surprises, circus charm, and magical moments! Two funny, sweet, and ageless clowns take the time to laugh, cry, and play; the time to exist. Through impressive balancing, contortion, diabolo, and hand-to-hand acts, this deeply human and comical work amazes children and gives adults a break from the frantic pace of everyday life.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Let yourself be enchanted by these two soft-funny friends, become part of their silly-silly games, and enjoy the magic of this timeless show. <span class=\"ItalicText\">Glob</span> is a show that explores the themes of waiting and the unknown, staging them in an imaginative, refined, and enchanting universe. Inspired by silent cinema and its essential icons: Charlie Chaplin, Buster Keaton, and Laurel and Hardy, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Glob</span> is a clown show magnificently sprinkled with poetry and light.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Glob</span> was created by <span class=\"BoldText\">Les Foutoukours</span>, one of the most popular companies in Quebec, which has created 20 shows in its 25 years of existence. Their shows have travelled all over the world, won awards, and, above all, the hearts of more than 500,000 spectators.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-23T18:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/files/23930890-bc37-40a6-acbb-a102abed26ea.jpg>;
